              <title xml:lang="per">&#x644;&#x637;&#x627;&#x626;&#x641; &#x627;&#x644;&#x644;&#x63A;&#x627;&#x62A;</title>
              <note>
                <p>A glossary of the <title>Masnav&#x12B;-&#x2019;i ma&#x2018;nav&#x12B;</title>, by <name type="person" role="author" xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="http://lccn.loc.gov/n81059876">Jal&#x101;l al-D&#x12B;n R&#x16B;m&#x12B;</name> (d. 672/1273). The work was compiled by &#x2018;Abd al-La&#x1E6D;&#x12B;f ibn &#x2018;Abd All&#x101;h al-&#x2018;Abb&#x101;s&#x12B;, also known as <name type="person" role="author" xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="http://lccn.loc.gov/n2011083741">Kab&#x12B;r&#x12B;yah Gujar&#x101;t&#x12B;</name> (d. 1048 or 1049/1638 or 1639). It deals with all the words in the Masnav&#x12B; that were not in his time used in everyday Persian, listing them in alphabetical order by the first and last letters. </p>
                <p>&#x2018;Abd al-La&#x1E6D;&#x12B;f al-&#x2018;Abb&#x101;s&#x12B;, who also produced a revised and annotated edition of the Masnav&#x12B; and a commentary on the difficult passages, took twelve years to compose the glossary, in which he was assisted by Mawl&#x101;n&#x101; Ibr&#x101;h&#x12B;m Dihlav&#x12B;.</p>
                <p>Other contents: f. 1r-2r, passages from a work on grammar and the usage of certain words; 2r and 2v, ownership seal; f. 222r-225, miscellaneous verses, etc.; 22v, tables of stations of the moon, names of Iranian months, etc. </p>
              </note>
